President Donald J. Trump hosted a working lunch in New York with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan and President Moon Jae-in of the Republic of Korea. The three leaders discussed the growing threats posed by North Korea's aggressive actions, including recent missile launches and a nuclear test. They pledged to implement United Nations Security Council Resolution 2375 and called on all countries to join their efforts to pressure North Korea. The leaders also emphasized that North Korea's actions have brought their nations closer together and affirmed their coordination in preparation for President Trump's upcoming visits to Japan and the Republic of Korea.